'''New Years Eve 2025''' is the ninth annual [[New Years Eve]] event held by [[VRChat]]. Users celebrate the 2025 New Year in an underwater-themed world. 

==Background==
On November 1st 2024, VRChat announced that content submissions for the 2025 New Years world would open on November 5th, 2024. Confirming the event would return for it's ninth year.<ref>[https://x.com/VRChat/status/1852418033546870976 NYE25 Submissions Announcement]</ref>

Included in the announcement, VRChat shared the type of submissions users can submit, along with guidelines<ref>[https://vrch.at/nye-2025-requirements NYE25 Submissions Guidelines]</ref> to follow for submissions to be accepted. The type of submissions users can submit are Posters, Booths, Graffiti, and videos for the VRChat Entertainment Network. The deadline for submissions was on December 6th, 2024.

A webpage<ref name="NYE25 Announcement" /> and video<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/shorts/uKe4t6ohK0E NYE25 Promo Video]</ref> was released on December 23rd, 2024, promoting the New Years event and revealing the theme.

==World==
The world was released on December 31st, 2024, along with a world row.<ref>[https://x.com/VRChat/status/1873847767199518728 NYE25 Release Timing]</ref> The world came with three separate versions, a [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_115508ad-9fae-4ee5-a001-6dd72beb9ba7 low capacity], [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_64c17705-a5c0-46f5-acae-8760dc13092e max capacity], and an [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_7f217a3b-b8a7-4bc4-ab11-02ba8c3a4043 unlocked URL] version.

=== Posters, Booths, and Graffiti ===
Posters, Booths, and Graffiti are scattered throughout the world which were submitted by the community. The world contains 122 posters, 19 booths, and 100+ graffiti.

=== Entertainment Network ===
During the event, VRChat streamed the Entertainment Network on their Twitch stream which was also displayed in the low, high capacity versions of the world. It contained 15 hours and 44 minutes of footage.

=== Quests ===
Users can complete quests by fishing and interacting with [[VRCat]] around the world. Users can track their quest progress on the quest board near the spawn.

